    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a superlative example of the golden era of Japanese performance. It features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting optimal compression across both rotors and a factory-spec power delivery. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring peak power transfer. The lightweight chassis retains its original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension, offering the telepathic handling and 50/50 weight distribution this platform is renowned for. Meticulously preserved, the vehicle shows no evidence of heat-cycling fatigue in the vacuum lines or oxidation on the undercarriage. This is a mechanically transparent, unmodified specimen that represents the pinnacle of rotary engineering.",
